caption: Staff is amazing!

The photos looked really good so we decided to stop by but the taste, quality and authenticity nope not even close. I got small bits of chicken supposedly tikka, but there was nothing on it and the yellow rice not sure what flavor it was taste just old. Got some hot sauce definitely not close to any Indian flavor. Was pricey for the quality. Wouldnt waste money again here.
Friendly service and delicious wraps, the bread was especially tasty!

This place serves kaathi rolls in its true original Kolkata taste and form. Tried this place for the first time today and became a fan instantaneously. The chilli chicken roll is worth every $. The hot sauce is a revelation. Even though it is quite spicy and hot, the mustard oil gives it a sharp edge.

They are rolling chicken in Indian bread but it is not a kaathi roll. They are cooking egg and bread seperately and resulting flavor is more of like confused burrito. I took chilli chicken and paneer roll, first of all the servers don't know how to roll the thing nicely, they more of a making it in a sandwich style and paneer roll was pathetic, no Indian spices nothing, chicken was still better.

We ordered online at this place last night, for a pick up. On reaching the store around 7.30 we find that the place is closed and there is a board outside saying they are closed due to a strike. I never got my order for which I paid in full and besides the inconvenience was not worth it. What a rip off! Unprofessional and unethical  Update: the owner reached out to me after seeing my review and he took care of the refund. I appreciate the prompt attention to the matter. We like the food at Kathi and look forward to ordering again.
What a great place!  We were walking by and decided to give it a try.  The food is amazing — delicious sauces and all house made.  Highly recommend the chili chicken and the mango shake!
Thanks Aditya! Will check it out.
Always good!

The service is very slow. Here at lunchtime and there’s one employee answering phones,  cooking, dealing with customers.  He was in the back cleaning when I got here.  Need another employee to help out. I was here for 10 min before he took my order.
I ordered paneer rolls, really liked the paratha bread and hot sauce. The food was fresh and good. The service was great.

the food is great! fresh tasting, light yet filling.  everything is priced competitively, with large portions for a low price.  spice can vary based on personal preference. i highly recommend the mango smoothie with your food!

We ordered food from Kaathi rolls for our cricket team, pleasantly surprised by the quality and taste of the rolls and the fusion style samosa’s, Everyone wants a repeat order the following week! Great customer service and follow ups! Hoping to try all of your menu in the coming weeks!! From: Satisfied customer on behalf of a team!

Didn't want to bring your rating downs but that's the best I can give. Honestly food was expensive. Wasn't ready when I arrived at my pick up time but I don't mind. When I recieved the food I was surprised my $20 order was in a small bag lol. I had to ask her to make sure was that all. Wedges were under cooked the big ones specially. Not a fan of seasoning on the wedges I'd rather just eat normal fries. The wrap and samosa was a so-so nothing special. Mango shake wasn't a fan either as it seemed like it consisted more milk and cream then mango. I didn't really like the flavor or concept but wish you the best during this difficult time of covid.

Amazing food 👌 I had 3 single rolls which I couldn't finish the third one. Portion sizes are hardy. I had the Chicken Tikka, Masala and the Pepper Lamb which was my favorite.  I'm not usually a fan of lamb but this was very flavorful with out the gamy bitter taste. The sauces are very tasty and each giving the food a different dynamic.
I adore this restaurant a lot. there is a friendly feeling. The kitcen is good. the service is dynamic and the team is trained. The price is honest. extremely recommend.

Everything was delicious. We tried the chicken tikka paratha rolls, the chicken masala rolls, the paneer bowl, the veggie coconut samosas, and wedges! It was all so good! They were really busy but the service was excellent. Highly recommend checking them out!

I had an issue with my order, and despite having additional issues with the general managers, the owner promptly reached out to me to correct my order and even added an additional item to make up for it. The food itself is delicious, and I greatly appreciate the professionalism from the owner.
Great food!
Undercooked. Missing item. Just okay.
We order the samosas, chickpea salad, mango shake, and/or paneer rolls from here about three times per week, and it never gets old. Wonderful product!

Kaathis provided an amazing lunch to our hospital staff yesterday. Everything was super fresh, the flavors were vibrant and wonderfully balanced, and the portions (2 rolls) were perfect. I was lucky enough to try one of the chili chicken and one of the poblano-potato rolls - both were fantastic. Plenty of other protein and vegetarian options on the menu as well. Aditya was friendly and so excited to support us during this trying time for healthcare. I'll be ordering his meal delivery service starting next week to have a week's supply of meals from his and other small restaurants delivered. Thanks, Kaathis!
I honestly enjoy the dishes and service, excellent area next to my house. The employees are always welcoming. Will come visit again.

Went with my son recently - we got the chicken Tikka masala bowl and the chili chicken bowl. Both dishes were quite disappointing. Overseasoned to the point where we couldn't tell which was what. Below average service as well. If you're looking for good Indian in the neighborhood, walk over to Rangoli on Clark & Fullerton.
Not even close to real Kathi rolls. Feels tht the The bread is frozen and just heated .... No value for money!!! Nd worst part is roll is tiny ....
Delicious & affordable
The service here was ok, the food was not. Small place, could seriously use some improvement.
Would certainly recommend visiting this place. Fantastic vibes, delightful food, fantastic service. Great work.
Vegetarian Food isn't that great.
Paneer roll was absolutely bland, had raw slices of onions, no sauce at all. Paneer was not flavored too. Couldn’t eat!
Delicious Indian kaati rolls! Vegetarian, vegan, non vegetarian - they cater to everyone! Loved their cauliflower roll best of all. The owner is very sweet, gracious and welcoming.
Small quantity of food and they didn't provide the sides I ordered.
Awesome food! It’s like a home cooked meal with a flair! Gotta taste it for yourself! ❤️❤️❤️❤️❤️❤️❤️❤️❤️❤️❤️❤️❤️❤️❤️❤️
Delicious!! 😋
Thank you for bringing the warmth of Kolkata street food to Chicago! The food is as authentic as it is tasty! Looking forward to more additions to the menu from our beloved hometown!
Love the food here. Every bite takes me back to the deliciousness of Kolkata!

One of our favorite places for delivery and take out.  Their lamb rolls with a little bit of extra spice on request added and the chutney hits the spot every single time!  Our second favorite are the beef rolls. Tender, very well seasoned and a little bit of dunk in chutney will leave you wanting more.  Suggestion would be to order 2-3 at a time. I can promise you will finish them off and still want more. Not because they are small in size but more so because they are just that GOOD!!

Kaathis is amazing!! The food is delicious and it’s not greasy like other places I’ve tried in the past. Their chicken chili and the gobi roll is my favorite. The chili sauce is soooo good. They actually have a very nice selection of sides to choose from. This is my to go place in Chicago. So happy to have found this place. The owner is very nice too.
++Good tasty food!!; -small portions; -take out preferred
Fresh food at a Fast casual restaurant and prices are great
Kaathis restaurant has the best flavorful food ever! Quickly and efficiently prepared I’m never disappointed in the service or taste of this place.
i loved the food here ! My mouth was literally bursting with flavors . & they have really great customer service👍🏽

Great place for Indian comfort food. Lots of options to chose from menu. Had Paneer roll and Gobi roll. Both were delicious and paneer was really fresh. mango shake is amazing! Definitely will return soon
We had the Paneer makhani roll & Mango shake, its good tasty food. A bit pricey to the size of the portions, but will order again.. Keep up guys..

I’m surprised to see the negative reviews here because my husband and I had the complete opposite experience. I heard that Kaathis was a new restaurant that serves halal food and is open late on Friday nights so my husband and I decided to check it out. It’s a nice mellow place among a street full of bars and pubs so it was nice having some peace and quiet. The decor inside was very modern and nice. We ordered a beef paratha roll and a paneer makhani bowl with a mango shake. The food was AMAZING! I’ll admit, I was a little surprised to see that they use frozen parathas and maybe they should try making them fresh from scratch? But I normally don’t like to eat South Asian food when I go out because that’s something I can easily make/get at home without paying for it but their food was so flavorful and so delicious that I would definitely go back again! The combination of unique flavors they add to their items makes it so different from what you’d get at you typical Indian restaurant and it’s the perfect place to go for a quick bite! The owner was very kind and friendly and constantly checked up on us to ask if we needed anything else. When we went, they had a playlist of all of the classic Bollywood songs and it really made dining in more enjoyable. I was enjoying the songs so much that I didn’t want to leave even after having finished my meal because it made me feel nostalgic about my childhood listening to those old songs. I would highly recommend checking out Kaathis!
Average food taste

The person at counter took too long time to deliver the order. The price was too expensive for the quality and the quantity they give. Also, the recipes are not fresh made and they have been taking from the frozen food and use to make Kaathi wraps/rolls.

The rolls tasted good but they are priced too high. Also the staff seems to be disinterested. I read recent reviews and still gave it a shot but after my experience I can totally understand why this place is going down the hill. The management needs to take keen interest in running affairs of this place if they want it back running.
How can you say “sorry we are out” during lunchtime when the hours on your door clearly state you’re open. Ridiculous.

PLEASE DO NOT EAT HERE! The rolls I receive, the bread was under cook and doughy. They microwaved my bowl which made the food disgusting! Sometimes the food tastes a day old or more.  I will never remind this place to anyone.
Great place to work, and the food is off the chain. The best authentic Indian food from India recipes made from scratch. Doesn't get any better than that.
I am not suppose to give this one star ...  The Kolkata rice was raw and not cooked properly . They serve frozen naan served in form of roll.. Please don’t waste your money and time in this place..
The cauliflower salad and paneer makhani roll were amazing!
Lotta things, but I knew it was game over when my bowl had to be put in the microwave. Just happy I got jersey mikes after I threw away my pepper lamb bowl

First ever review. Worst place. Worst service. There was just one more couple waiting on order besides us so clearly they were not busy and still managed to mess up my order 3 times in a row after repeatedly telling them that I wanted a paneer bowl. At first they gave chili chicken bowl then they gave a chicken kathi roll then they gave a poblano pepper bowl. I mean I just don’t understand how can they mess it up after repeatedly telling them what we needed.
Great food and also great staff and awesome boss

(Translated by Google) Excellent scent when we go home, but if I'm going to give one day to savor the best dishes thanks 😃😃💎💎💎💎🙂🙂🙂🙂🙂  (Original) Exelente el aroma cuando pasamos ya para casa ,pero si me voy a regalar un día para saborear de los mejores platillos gracias 😃😃💎💎💎💎🙂🙂🙂🙂🙂

I was not impressed with this place. The rice bowl (pulao I think) didn’t taste good. Although the menu said it comes with a chickpea salad and mint chutney, they were both missing in mine. The roll was also okay-ish. The chicken filling wasn’t that tasty. I was looking forward to trying this place out, but I was disappointed.
The food was incredible and the server was so sweet! If I lived in Chicago, I’d eat here more often.
Good cozy place with character. Food is amazing and surprisingly all items are low priced.
You feel welcomed , by the staff ! The food is absolutely amazing . From the refreshing mango shake , down to the flaky parathas you’ll love every roll !!

Looks like they make rolls in the morning instead of making them per order, refrigerat it, and then put them in the oven for a minute or two to warm up  Flavor of food is spot on but cold filling left a bad impression. All warming up food in aluminum foil does is, takes the moisture out of meat and leaves it rubbery.
Bad imitation of Naansense. The food quality and taste is bad. Don’t bother with this place.
Disappointing taste.

Yup, this is one of my favorite spots. They just officially opened today and it’s nice to have a gem in Lincoln Park. I personally know the owner and he is a phenomenal person. I got the beef and chili chicken roll which is wrapped on a paratha which is like a flatbread. The beef and chicken were seasoned perfectly but you can also ask for it to be spicy. You have been warned - if you request spicy, you will get what you asked for. They have other options as well but this I would recommend starting with the rolls. Here is a plus: the interiors of the restaurant is very cozy (I even attached a picture as proof).
They were offering some free samples, so we stopped in, tried out the food, and chatted with the owners. The food was fantastic (I love Indian), and they were so friendly. We'll be back!

Mango shake is really refreshing and goes well with kaathis rolls. Mango shake is the best tasting drink I have ever tasted. The rolls are always hot, fresh, and ready. My favorite roll is the beef. It consist of beef, onion, cilantro, and lime juice on paratha. Which is healthy and fulfilling. The rice is also very good and different from what we’re all use to. I highly recommend kaathis.
Amazing food!
Kaathis were made with fresh ingredients. We ordered various kinds of Kaathis, and they delivered each of them as it was ordered. Certainly would recommend this place to anyone.
Delicious rolls at a very resealable cost !! i knew i would need more than just 2 rolls right after my very first bite of paneer rolls.
Great taste and flavourful. Tried veg and paneer rolls. Both were good. They have spicy option also, in case you like more spicy. Good service as well.
Had their Chicken Tikka and Beef Kaathi roll, it was very delicious and all ingredients tasted fresh. Priced right and fulfilling. Will definitely go there again.
Great place to eat. Great food. Great team in kitchen. Stop on by.
The food is fantastic. Very flavorful. I highly recommend catering from them honestly.

The foods from Kaathis are delicious - completely flavorful tastes.  The care and artistry in preparapation make the experience that much more enjoyable.  I find the choices perfect for lunches near the loop.  Chicago is better for this jewel - don't detail, order soon and enjoy!

Best Ever!! I was tried pretty much all the kathi roll joints in Chicago, nothing comes close to this. My favorite is the Chilli chicken roll and cauliflower roll...sooo yum! and ohhhh the mint chutney is to die for!!
Great Paneer and Chicken kaathi rolls !!
